hnology101-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kary_B._Mullis#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> The improvements made by Mullis allowed PCR to become a central technique in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Biochemistry\" title=\"Biochemistry\">biochemistry<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Molecular_biology\" title=\"Molecular biology\">molecular biology<\/a>, described by <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_New_York_Times\" title=\"The New York Times\">The New York Times<\/a><\/i> as \"highly original and significant, virtually dividing biology into the two epochs of before P.C.R. and after P.C.R.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-NYTimes1998_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kary_B._Mullis#cite_note-NYTimes1998-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>Since winning the Nobel Prize, Mullis has been criticized in <i>The New York Times<\/i> for promoting ideas in areas in which he has no expertise.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NYT_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kary_B._Mullis#cite_note-NYT-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He has promoted <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/AIDS_denialism\" title=\"AIDS denialism\" class=\"mw-redirect\">AIDS denialism<\/a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Naked_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kary_B._Mullis#cite_note-Naked-7\"><span>[<\/span>7<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Find_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kary_B._Mullis#cite_note-Find-8\"><span>[<\/span>8<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Informer_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kary_B._Mullis#cite_note-Informer-9\"><span>[<\/span>9<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Kalichman_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a h